As you know, thanks to our community voting, ReformDAO has made a strategic decision: transitioning from realized profits-based buybacks to rebate-based buybacks, combined with a shift to daily buybacks. This isn’t just operational, it’s a game-changer for $RFRM and its community. Here’s why. 

Why move from realized profits to rebates? 
Realized profits are uncertain: They depend heavily on market conditions and price movements. This means there’s no guarantee of consistent funds for buybacks.

Rebates are reliable: They accumulate over time, regardless of market fluctuations. This ensures a constant, predictable flow of funds to support the ecosystem.

Rebates remove the insecurity and unpredictability of relying on realized profits.

Why daily buybacks? 
Under the old model, buybacks happened in a single event after a long wait. While impactful, it left the rest of the period without any support.

With daily buybacks:
• Consistent Buying Pressure: Instead of one big buyback day, there’s steady buying pressure every day.
• Stability: Daily buybacks create continuous growth and confidence rather than short-lived spikes.

Why this is better for the community:
For existing investors:
• Rebates provide a stable and predictable system.
• Daily buybacks maintain steady price support and reduce volatility.

For new investors:
• $RFRM is backed by an even more sustainable, consistent system.
• Daily buybacks signal commitment and transparency, attracting long-term believers.

Rebates + Daily Buybacks = A Better System 
By shifting away from realized profits to rebates and adopting daily buybacks, we’ve built a model that:
• Ensures a constant flow of support for $RFRM.
• Aligns token performance with consistent, predictable actions.

This move isn’t just about a single shift in our ecosystem, it’s about creating a reliable, sustainable future for $RFRM.

No more waiting for market conditions. 
No more uncertainty. Just daily action and steady growth.

Rebates power the system. Daily buybacks sustain it. Together, they make $RFRM stronger every day.
